## Coverage simulation

### Design

The simulation grid is identical to the [previous post](/posts/bls-bootstrap-validation/): four baseline rates, three sample sizes, and one confirmation condition. Fieller's CI is added as a third method evaluated on the same replicated datasets. Replications where $x_1 = 0$ or $x_0 = 0$ are skipped for all methods.

| Parameter            | Values                                  |
|----------------------|-----------------------------------------|
| $RR$                 | $1.20$ (primary), $1.50$ (confirmation) |
| $p_0$                | $0.02, \; 0.05, \; 0.10, \; 0.20$       |
| $n \; (= n_1 = n_0)$ | $100, \; 500, \; 2{,}000$               |
| Replications         | $K = 10{,}000$                          |
| Confidence level     | $95\%$                                  |

For Fieller, an unbounded CI (where $a \leq 0$) is counted as covering the true $RR$, since the confidence set includes all real values. The rate of unbounded CIs is reported separately.

